Female:
Similar to male except normal sexual dimorphism and as follows: frons yellow with medial triangular brown macula towards ocellar triangle not reaching posterior black area, black lateral margin on posterior half (
Fig. 82
); posterior section of anepimeron dark; abdominal fasciae narrower without emargination, tergum 4 with yellow fascia very sinuate medially (
Fig. 84
).
